{
  // A descriptive name for your development container.
  "name": "Yeab Game Zone Ludo Bot",
  
  // This is the most important part. It tells Codespaces to use the
  // docker-compose.yml file located in this same .github/ folder to build the environment.
  "dockerComposeFile": "docker-compose.yml",
  
  // This specifies that 'app' is the main service from your docker-compose.yml file.
  // When you open Codespaces, your terminal will be inside this container.
  "service": "app",
  
  // This sets the default directory that will be opened in your VS Code terminal.
  "workspaceFolder": "/workspace",
  
  // This section customizes the VS Code editor that runs inside Codespaces.
  "customizations": {
    "vscode": {
      "settings": {
        // --- Code Quality & Formatting ---
        "python.pythonPath": "/usr/local/bin/python",
        "python.linting.pylintEnabled": true,
        "python.linting.enabled": true,
        "python.formatting.provider": "autopep8", // Automatically format your code
        "[python]": {
          "editor.formatOnSave": true // Format your Python code every time you save
        }
      },
      // --- Recommended Extensions ---
      // This ensures that every developer working on the project has the same
      // essential extensions for Python development.
      "extensions": [
        "ms-python.python",       // The official Python extension from Microsoft
        "ms-python.vscode-pylance", // Provides rich language features like IntelliSense
        "ms-azuretools.vscode-docker" // Useful for managing Docker containers
      ]
    }
  },
  
  // This command runs automatically *after* the development container has been created.
  // It installs all the Python packages from your requirements.txt file.
  "postCreateCommand": "pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt",
  
  // This sets the default user inside the container for security and permission reasons.
  "remoteUser": "vscode"
}```

### What Makes This Version Perfect:

1.  **Automatic Code Formatting:** The new lines `python.formatting.provider` and `editor.formatOnSave` are a major improvement. Now, every time you save a Python file, the editor will automatically clean up your code to follow standard Python style guides. This keeps your code consistent and professional.
2.  **Clear, Detailed Comments:** The entire file is now commented, explaining what each setting does and why it's important. This makes it much easier to understand and maintain.
3.  **Essential Extensions:** It includes the most important VS Code extensions for a productive Python development workflow, ensuring that your environment is fully featured right from the start.

This configuration will give you a smooth, professional, and highly productive development environment every time you open your project in GitHub Codespaces.